# What is Landsat 9?

.pull-left[

Launched: September 27, 2021.

Mission: A joint NASA/USGS mission to continue the ~50-year record of Earth observation. [web:4][web:2]

Legacy: Successor to Landsat 8, replacing the aging Landsat 7 to maintain a two-satellite constellation. [web:4]

Design: Essentially a “clone” of Landsat 8 with improved hardware and calibration. [web:2]
]

