# Application 2: Water Quality

### Detecting Algal Blooms and Coastal Changes

.panelset[
.panel[.panel-name[Overview]

#### Purpose
* **Dark Target Monitoring**: Specialize in coastal waters and inland lakes.
* **Health & Safety**: Early detection of Harmful Algal Blooms (HABs) that affect drinking water and recreation.

#### Why Landsat 9?
* **14-bit Quantization**: OLI-2 is a game-changer. Because water is a "dark" target (low reflectance), higher sensitivity allows for detecting chlorophyll and sediments with much higher precision.
]

.panel[.panel-name[Key Takeaway]

> **Precision in the Shadows**: The increased radiometric resolution means we can see "into" the water better than ever before, distinguishing between murky sediment and dangerous algal growth in complex coastal environments.
]
]

---

# Landsat 8 vs. Landsat 9

### Technical Evolution

| Feature | Landsat 8 | Landsat 9 |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Quantization** | 12-bit | **14-bit** (Higher sensitivity) |
| **TIRS Design** | Risk Class C | **Risk Class B** (Higher reliability) |
| **Stray Light** | Known issue | **Corrected** in TIRS-2 |
| **Scenes/Day** | ~740 | **~750** |
| **Launch** | Feb 2013 | **Sept 2021** |

